# Phase 3: Frontend UI & Forms Walkthrough

## Overview
Successfully implemented the complete frontend UI for the Purchase Order Management System, matching the requested design and functionality.

## Accomplishments

### 1. App Layout & Navigation
- **Sidebar**: Created a responsive sidebar with navigation links (Dashboard, POs, Suppliers, Products).
- **Layout**: Integrated the sidebar into the main app layout.
- **Theme**: Configured global styles with shadcn/ui and Tailwind CSS.
- **Components**: Installed all necessary shadcn components (Button, Input, Table, Dialog, Form, Toast, etc.).

### 2. Master Data Management
- **Suppliers Page**:
    - Data Table with search and actions.
    - Add/Edit Dialog with form validation (Zod).
    - Delete functionality with confirmation.
- **Products Page**:
    - Data Table with search and actions.
    - Add/Edit Dialog with form validation (Zod).
    - SKU duplicate check handles by API (backend validation).

### 3. Purchase Order Management
- **PO List Page**:
    - List of POs with Status Badges (Draft, Approved, Sent, Cancelled).
    - "Create New PO" button.
    - View details link (eye icon).
    - Delete action (only for Draft status).
- **Create PO Page (Core Feature)**:
    - **Dynamic Form**: Add/remove product items dynamically.
    - **Real-time Calculations**: Subtotal, VAT (7%), and Grand Total update instantly as you change quantity/price.
    - **Validation**: Ensures supplier selection and at least one item.
    - **Date Pickers**: Issue Date and Delivery Date fields.

### 4. Phase 4: PDF Generation
- **PDF Template**: Created a professional A4 [POTemplate](file:///d:/Workshop/po/src/components/pdf/POTemplate.tsx#157-261) component using `@react-pdf/renderer`.
- **PO Details Page**:
    - Displays full PO information.
    - **Download PDF**: Generates the PDF client-side with dynamic data.
    - **Status Workflow**: Added "Approve PO" button to transition from DRAFT to APPROVED.

### 5. Verification
- **Build**: TypeScript compilation passed with zero errors.
- **Components**: All shadcn components installed and verified.
- **Routes**:
